# WPF + Prism MVVM (Lyrixound)

## ViewModel resolution

Views set `prism:ViewModelLocator.AutoWireViewModel="True"`. The locator pairs `Lyrixound.Views.FooWindow` with `Lyrixound.ViewModels.FooWindowViewModel` (and `Views.Bar` with `ViewModels.BarViewModel`) by convention. To add a new view-model pair, just name the class accordingly; no manual registration is required for the VM itself.

Dependencies (services, settings, watchers) come in via VM constructor. They're already registered in `App.xaml.cs > RegisterTypes`. If you need a new dependency type, register it there first.

## Bindable properties

Use Prism `BindableBase` + `SetProperty`:

```csharp
private bool _searchInProgress;
public bool SearchInProgress
{
    get => _searchInProgress;
    set => SetProperty(ref _searchInProgress, value);
}
```

For derived properties (e.g. `FontStyle` from `IsItalic`), explicitly `RaisePropertyChanged(nameof(FontStyle))` from the source setter - see `LyricsSettingsViewModel`.

## Commands

Use `DelegateCommand` with `ObservesProperty` so CanExecute updates automatically when bound state changes:

```csharp
FindLyricsCommand = new DelegateCommand(async () => await FindLyricsAsync(), CanFindLyrics)
    .ObservesProperty(() => Track.Artist)
    .ObservesProperty(() => Track.Title)
    .ObservesProperty(() => SearchInProgress);
```

Don't swallow exceptions in async command bodies - log them; the dispatcher handler in `App.OnDispatcherUnhandledException` is the last resort.

## Code-behind

Code-behind in `Views/*.xaml.cs` is reserved for view-only concerns: drag/move, click-through P/Invoke (`WS_EX_TRANSPARENT`/`WS_EX_NOACTIVATE`), scroll-to-center for synced lyrics, tray-icon glue. Do **not** put business logic, lyrics search, or audio recognition there.

## XAML

- Prefer Material Design controls (`md:PackIcon`, `MaterialDesignRaisedButton`, `MaterialDesignFlatButton`, etc.).
- Window is `AllowsTransparency="True"` + `WindowStyle="None"`; the title bar is custom (`Grid Name="TitleBar"`). Don't add chrome.
- Bind synced-lyric formatting via `RelativeSource AncestorType=Window` so it follows `LyricsSettings` regardless of `ListBox` container DataContext.
- Use `BooleanToVisibilityConverter` / `InverseBooleanToVisibilityConverter` (from `Converters/`) - don't add new visibility converters.

## Dispatcher

When a property setter triggers heavy UI work, marshal via `Application.Current.Dispatcher.BeginInvoke(...)` (see `TrackViewModel.Lyrics` setter rebuilding `LyricLines`).
